namic Title Updates\n   494\t- NFR-06: Code Quality Standards\n   495\t**Priority:** Could Have features for advanced user experience\n   496\t**Prerequisite:** Phase 1 complete\n   497\t\n   498\t## Glossary\n   499\t\n   500\t### SPA (Single Page Application)\n   501\t**Definition:** A web application that loads a single HTML page and dynamically updates content as the user interacts.\n   502\t**Source:** context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:34\n   503\t\n   504\t### Vue.js\n   505\t**Definition:** A progressive JavaScript framework for building user interfaces with reactive data binding.\n   506\t**Source:** context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:29\n   507\t\n   508\t### ES6+/ECMAScript 2015+\n   509\t**Definition:** Modern JavaScript standard with features like arrow functions, classes, and enhanced array methods.\n   510\t**Source:** context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:28\n   511\t\n   512\t### DOM (Document Object Model)\n   513\t**Definition:** Programming interface for HTML documents that represents the page structure as a tree of objects.\n   514\t**Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:20\n   515\t\n   516\t### Reactive Data Binding\n   517\t**Definition:** Automatic synchronization between data model and user interface elements.\n   518\t**Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:54\n   519\t\n   520\t### CSS Grid\n   521\t**Definition:** Two-dimensional layout system for creating responsive grid-based page layouts.\n   522\t**Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:39\n   523\t\n   524\t### Progressive Enhancement\n   525\t**Definition:** Web design strategy that provides basic functionality to all users while enhancing experience for those with modern browsers.\n   526\t**Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:150\n   527\t\n   528\t## Open Questions\n   529\t\n   530\t### OQ-01: Character Selection Criteria\n   531\t**Question:** What specific criteria should be used for selecting the 